      "body": "<font class=\"subject\"> <strong></strong> </font> <br /> <br /> <div class=\"mediumtxt\">Scarlet, installer only works with old mysql extention, but there no issues(none that I've seen yet) with MySQLi when you port your forums without purging old database.<br /> Temporary solutions while installer is being fixed would be:<ol type=\"A\"><br /> <li />Filling db details manually in config.php(assuming you already have an old xmb database)<br /> <li />Switching to PHP 5.6 in order to fulfil the installation and then switch back to PHP 7.x for usage and testing.<br /> </ol><br /> Anyway, to avoid unnecessary errors, MySQLi should be used by default, because both PHP 5 and PHP 7 supports it, while old MySQL is only supported prior to 7.0<br /> <br /> MySQL is deprecated(5.5.0)/removed(7.0.0) for a reason, it's outdated and not fitting current day standards, if it was up to me, I would remove it's support completely within a next stable beta. For those who still keen enough to use outdated php versions like 4.0 that doesn't have MySQLi, well, there's nothing wrong with usage of XMB 1.9.11, but tbh I haven't seen a host provider that still offers PHP 4 in a while.<img src='./images/smilies/smile.gif' style='border:none' alt=':)' /> Most of non old-school scripts now use either PDO or Mysqli, like IPS Community suite(or known as IPB in the past), Xenforo and etc.</div>",
