he VPS... </td></tr></table><br /> <br /> MariaDB is fully backward-compatible(at least supposed to be according to the docs) with MySQL server. It's basically just a fork of MySQL, so moving data should not be a hassle at all.<br /> <br /> <br /> P.S. To run XMB with mysqli any 5.x.x should do &amp; not just 5.6, but obviously newer versions contains fixes and optimisations.<br /> <br /> <br /> </div>",
